Subject: EveryBus 2002 Thanks

EB02 is over.

There were well over 160 VW Transporters in attendance and one very 
COOL MB Marco Polo Westfalia conversion with German registration and 
plates.

Thanks are in order for
Judy for 3 grueling days of registration
Cassady, Vickie and Tootsie for making kids happy and helping with 
the door prizes.
Mad Uncle Dave for Taking care of the Chili contest
The nice lady with crew cab for picking up my slack and winning the 
Chili cook off.
The Full Moon Bus Club for feeding hundreds of hungry folks on 
Saturday Morning.
The Canadians for feeding hundreds of hungry people on Sunday morning 
and teaching us all what bacon is really about!
Tom and Dana for handling the peoples choice awards.
Free Coffee-bus Man for keeping us all pumped up and getting me out 
of a serious jam!
Kurt for running the 50/50 raffle that raised money for type2,FMBC, 
and the vanagon list.
Steve Dolan for checking the dwell and timing on more poorly running 
buses than could keep count of and the space on the everybus server.
Andy for bringing his family all that way to brighten my day!
Buddah, MUD, the hippie chicks from the upper mid-west and others for 
making ice and medicine runs!!!!!
HST staff for providing a great facility.
Chad, Grace, Jeff and Judy for cleaning up.
Red cups and various brewing companies.
My friends and family for dealing with all my nuttiness!
Nikki for almost getting there.
Everyone in attendance for being there and for staying cooling when 
things got hot!
All the nice folks that donated door prizes and Bus Depot and Real 
speed for donating vendor prizes.
Richard for the shirts and Greg Potts for the .pdf.

There is no better group of people and I thank you all for making EB possible.

Chris




